{"title_page": "Jagdeep Singh (basketball)", "text_new": "{{Infobox basketball biography\n| photo = \n| caption = \n| position = [[Center (basketball)|Center]]\n| name = Jagdeep Singh\n| number = 6\n| height_ft = 6\n| height_in = 6\n| weight_lb = 213\n| team = Mumbai Challengers\n| league = [[UBA Pro Basketball League]]\n| nationality = Indian\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1986|1|10}}\n| birth_place = [[Sri Ganganagar|Sri Ganganagar, Rajasthan]]\n| highschool = Ludhiana Basketball Academy <br> ([[Ludhiana|Ludhiana, Punjab]])\n| college = \n| draft_year = \n| draft_team = \n| career_start = 2008\n| career_end = 2012\n| years1 = 2008\u20132012\n| team1 = [[FC Punjab Police|Punjab Police]]\n| years2 = [[2016 UBA Pro Basketball League season|2016]]\u2013present\n| team2 = Mumbai Challengers\n| highlights =\n* Indian All-Star (2011)\n}}\n\n'''Lebron singh''' ({{lang-hi|\u091c\u0917\u0926\u0940\u092a \u0938\u093f\u0902\u0939}}; born January 10, 1986) is former captain of Indian basketball team and an Indian professional [[basketball]] player for the Mumbai Challengers of the [[UBA Pro Basketball League]]. He spent his first seven seasons with Punjab Police Jalandhar in the [[Indian National Basketball Championship for Men|Indian National Basketball Championship]]. Singh was dismissed from Punjab in 2012 and suffered a career-threatening injury. He returned to basketball in 2016, when he signed with the Challengers. Singh competes with the [[India national basketball team]] at the [[FIBA Asia Championship]]. He has played with the team on over 20 occasions.\nBains has just completed his degree of coaching from national institute of sports , Patiala in 2019.\n\n== Early life ==\nSingh was born on January 10, 1986 in [[Sri Ganganagar|Sri Ganganagar, Rajasthan]].<ref name=\"pays\">{{cite web|last1=Teja|first1=Gagan K.|title=Bains pays for sticking with Punjab|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2014/20140620/sports.htm#6|website=[[The Tribune (Chandigarh)|The Tribune]]|accessdate=November 13, 2016|date=June 19, 2014}}</ref> His father coached [[sport of athletics|athletics]], and Jagdeep was a runner. Due to his exceptional height, he drew the attention of a local basketball coach in 2002. Singh joined the Rajasthan team in the following year, competing in school nationals.<ref name=\"interview\">{{cite web|last1=Dwivedi|first1=Aditi|title=\"Heartbreaking when you do so much, but get rejection in return,\" Jagdeep Singh Bains, ex India basketball player|url=http://ekalavyas.com/2015/07/12/jagdeep-singh-india-basketball-interview/|website=Ekalavyas.com|accessdate=November 13, 2016|date=July 12, 2015}}</ref> He was soon noticed by coach Sankaran Subramanian, and he was invited to the prestigious Ludhiana Basketball Academy in [[Ludhiana|Ludhiana, Punjab]].<ref name=pays/><ref name=\"ludhiana\">{{cite web|last1=Kanthwali|first1=Gaurav|title=Ludhiana provides wings to India's basketball dream|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/more-sports/others/Ludhiana-provides-wings-to-Indias-basketball-dream/articleshow/9889961.cms|website=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=November 13, 2016|date=September 7, 2011}}</ref> Subramanian trained Singh for five to six hours each day, and he taught him fundamental basketball skills.<ref name=interview/>\n\n== International career ==\nShortly after becoming a part of Ludhiana Basketball Academy early in his career, Singh joined the [[India national basketball team|India junior national team]]. At age 19, he became a member of the senior team.<ref name=pays/> Singh competed for India at both the [[FIBA Asia Championship 2007]] and [[FIBA Asia Championship 2009]].<ref>[http://china2009.fiba.com/pages/eng/fe/09/fascm/player/p/pid/64152/sid/7038/tid/301/profile.html FIBA Player Profile]</ref>  He averaged 11.4 points per game at the 2007 tournament for the 15th placed Indians.<ref>[http://china2009.fiba.com/pages/eng/fa/player/p/pid/64152/sid/3969/tid/301/_/2007_FIBA_Asia_Championship_for_Men/index.html FIBA Archive]</ref>  In 2009, he averaged a team-leading 7.8 rebounds per game as the Indian team improved to a 13th-place finish.<ref>[http://archive.fiba.com/pages/eng/fa/player/p/pid/64152/sid/7038/tid/301/_/2009_FIBA_Asia_Championship_for_Men/index.html FIBA Archive]</ref>  In both of India's victories, he was the game-leading rebounder, grabbing 10 against [[Indonesia national basketball team|Indonesia]] and 15 against [[Uzbekistan national basketball team|Uzbekistan]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://basketball.eurobasket.com/player/Jagdeep-Singh/India/Punjab-Police-Jalandhar/42352 Jagdeep Singh] at [[Eurobasket.com]]\n*[http://basketball.realgm.com/player/Jagdeep-Singh/Summary/25315 Jagdeep Singh] at [[RealGM]]\n\n{{India Squad 2011 FIBA Asia Championship}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Singh, Jagdeep}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:Young Cagers players]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Basketball players at the 2006 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Basketball players at the 2010 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Power forwards (basketball)]]\n[[Category:Centers (basketball)]]\n[[Category:Basketball players from Rajasthan]]\n[[Category:Asian Games competitors for India]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox basketball biography\n| photo = \n| caption = \n| position = [[Center (basketball)|Center]]\n| name = Jagdeep Singh\n| number = 6\n| height_ft = 6\n| height_in = 6\n| weight_lb = 213\n| team = Mumbai Challengers\n| league = [[UBA Pro Basketball League]]\n| nationality = Indian\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1986|1|10}}\n| birth_place = [[Sri Ganganagar|Sri Ganganagar, Rajasthan]]\n| highschool = Ludhiana Basketball Academy <br> ([[Ludhiana|Ludhiana, Punjab]])\n| college = \n| draft_year = \n| draft_team = \n| career_start = 2008\n| career_end = 2012\n| years1 = 2008\u20132012\n| team1 = [[FC Punjab Police|Punjab Police]]\n| years2 = [[2016 UBA Pro Basketball League season|2016]]\u2013present\n| team2 = Mumbai Challengers\n| highlights =\n* Indian All-Star (2011)\n}}\n\n'''Jagdeep Singh Bains''' ({{lang-hi|\u091c\u0917\u0926\u0940\u092a \u0938\u093f\u0902\u0939}}; born January 10, 1986) is former captain of Indian basketball team and an Indian professional [[basketball]] player for the Mumbai Challengers of the [[UBA Pro Basketball League]]. He spent his first seven seasons with Punjab Police Jalandhar in the [[Indian National Basketball Championship for Men|Indian National Basketball Championship]]. Singh was dismissed from Punjab in 2012 and suffered a career-threatening injury. He returned to basketball in 2016, when he signed with the Challengers. Singh competes with the [[India national basketball team]] at the [[FIBA Asia Championship]]. He has played with the team on over 20 occasions.\nBains has just completed his degree of coaching from national institute of sports , Patiala in 2019.\n\n== Early life ==\nSingh was born on January 10, 1986 in [[Sri Ganganagar|Sri Ganganagar, Rajasthan]].<ref name=\"pays\">{{cite web|last1=Teja|first1=Gagan K.|title=Bains pays for sticking with Punjab|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2014/20140620/sports.htm#6|website=[[The Tribune (Chandigarh)|The Tribune]]|accessdate=November 13, 2016|date=June 19, 2014}}</ref> His father coached [[sport of athletics|athletics]], and Jagdeep was a runner. Due to his exceptional height, he drew the attention of a local basketball coach in 2002. Singh joined the Rajasthan team in the following year, competing in school nationals.<ref name=\"interview\">{{cite web|last1=Dwivedi|first1=Aditi|title=\"Heartbreaking when you do so much, but get rejection in return,\" Jagdeep Singh Bains, ex India basketball player|url=http://ekalavyas.com/2015/07/12/jagdeep-singh-india-basketball-interview/|website=Ekalavyas.com|accessdate=November 13, 2016|date=July 12, 2015}}</ref> He was soon noticed by coach Sankaran Subramanian, and he was invited to the prestigious Ludhiana Basketball Academy in [[Ludhiana|Ludhiana, Punjab]].<ref name=pays/><ref name=\"ludhiana\">{{cite web|last1=Kanthwali|first1=Gaurav|title=Ludhiana provides wings to India's basketball dream|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/more-sports/others/Ludhiana-provides-wings-to-Indias-basketball-dream/articleshow/9889961.cms|website=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=November 13, 2016|date=September 7, 2011}}</ref> Subramanian trained Singh for five to six hours each day, and he taught him fundamental basketball skills.<ref name=interview/>\n\n== International career ==\nShortly after becoming a part of Ludhiana Basketball Academy early in his career, Singh joined the [[India national basketball team|India junior national team]]. At age 19, he became a member of the senior team.<ref name=pays/> Singh competed for India at both the [[FIBA Asia Championship 2007]] and [[FIBA Asia Championship 2009]].<ref>[http://china2009.fiba.com/pages/eng/fe/09/fascm/player/p/pid/64152/sid/7038/tid/301/profile.html FIBA Player Profile]</ref>  He averaged 11.4 points per game at the 2007 tournament for the 15th placed Indians.<ref>[http://china2009.fiba.com/pages/eng/fa/player/p/pid/64152/sid/3969/tid/301/_/2007_FIBA_Asia_Championship_for_Men/index.html FIBA Archive]</ref>  In 2009, he averaged a team-leading 7.8 rebounds per game as the Indian team improved to a 13th-place finish.<ref>[http://archive.fiba.com/pages/eng/fa/player/p/pid/64152/sid/7038/tid/301/_/2009_FIBA_Asia_Championship_for_Men/index.html FIBA Archive]</ref>  In both of India's victories, he was the game-leading rebounder, grabbing 10 against [[Indonesia national basketball team|Indonesia]] and 15 against [[Uzbekistan national basketball team|Uzbekistan]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://basketball.eurobasket.com/player/Jagdeep-Singh/India/Punjab-Police-Jalandhar/42352 Jagdeep Singh] at [[Eurobasket.com]]\n*[http://basketball.realgm.com/player/Jagdeep-Singh/Summary/25315 Jagdeep Singh] at [[RealGM]]\n\n{{India Squad 2011 FIBA Asia Championship}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Singh, Jagdeep}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:Young Cagers players]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Basketball players at the 2006 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Basketball players at the 2010 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Power forwards (basketball)]]\n[[Category:Centers (basketball)]]\n[[Category:Basketball players from Rajasthan]]\n[[Category:Asian Games competitors for India]]\n", "name_user": "Nbabasketball2345", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jagdeep_Singh_(basketball)"}
{"title_page": "Vachirawit Chiva-aree", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{short description|Thai actor, host, model and singer}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Vachirawit Chiva-aree\n| image              = Bbrightvc.jpg\n| imagesize          = 250px\n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = \n| native_name        = \u0e27\u0e0a\u0e34\u0e23\u0e27\u0e34\u0e0a\u0e0d\u0e4c \u0e0a\u0e35\u0e27\u0e2d\u0e32\u0e23\u0e35\n| native_name_lang   = tha\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1997|12|27}}\n| birth_place        = [[Nakhon Pathom]], Thailand\n| alma_mater         = \n| height             = {{height|ft=6|in=0.2}} <ref>{{cite web |title=Q&A|url=https://www.instagram.com/stories/highlights/17847833104423976/ |website=instagram.com |publisher= @bbrightvc|accessdate=March 27, 2020 |language=Thai |date=September 2018}}</ref>\n| other_names        = Bright\n| occupation         = Actor, [[Talk show host|Host]], Model, Singer\n| years_active       = 2013\u2013present\n| notable_works      = {{plainlist|\n* '''Young Peng''' in  ''[[My Ambulance]]''\n* '''Sarawat''' in ''[[2gether: The Series (Thai TV series)|2gether: The Series]]''\n}}\n| agent              = [[GMMTV]]\n| website            = \n}}\n\n'''Vachirawit Chiva-aree''' ({{lang-th|\u0e27\u0e0a\u0e34\u0e23\u0e27\u0e34\u0e0a\u0e0d\u0e4c \u0e0a\u0e35\u0e27\u0e2d\u0e32\u0e23\u0e35}}; also known as '''Bright''' ({{lang-th|\u0e44\u0e1a\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e17}}), born December 27, 1997) is a Thai actor, singer, host and model. He is best known for his role as a ''Young Peng'' in the television series ''[[My Ambulance]]'' (2019) and as ''Sarawat'' in ''[[2gether: The Series (Thai TV series)|2gether: The Series]]'' (2020), where he stars as [[Metawin Opas-iamkajorn]]'s love interest.\n\n==Early life and education==\nVachirawit was born on December 27, 1997 in [[Nakhon Pathom Province]], Thailand.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e27\u0e31\u0e15\u0e34 \"\u0e44\u0e1a\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e17 \u0e27\u0e0a\u0e34\u0e23\u0e27\u0e34\u0e0a\u0e0d\u0e4c\" \u0e17\u0e33\u0e04\u0e27\u0e32\u0e21\u0e23\u0e39\u0e49\u0e08\u0e31\u0e01\u0e19\u0e31\u0e01\u0e41\u0e2a\u0e14\u0e07\u0e14\u0e32\u0e27\u0e23\u0e38\u0e48\u0e07 \u0e2b\u0e19\u0e38\u0e48\u0e21\u0e44\u0e17\u0e22-\u0e2d\u0e40\u0e21\u0e23\u0e34\u0e01\u0e31\u0e19 \u0e08\u0e32\u0e01\u0e23\u0e31\u0e49\u0e27 \u0e21.\u0e01\u0e23\u0e38\u0e07\u0e40\u0e17\u0e1e |url=https://www.sanook.com/campus/1399611/ |website=sanook.com |publisher=Sanook |accessdate=March 15, 2020 |language=Thai |date=March 10, 2020}}</ref> He completed his secondary education in [[Suankularb Wittayalai School]]. He took up Thammasat English Engineering Programme (TEPE) under the Faculty of Engineering of [[Thammasat University]]. He is currently taking up Marketing (International Program) in [[Bangkok University]].<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e27\u0e0a\u0e34\u0e23\u0e27\u0e34\u0e0a\u0e0d\u0e4c \u0e0a\u0e35\u0e27\u0e2d\u0e32\u0e23\u0e35 (\u0e44\u0e1a\u0e23\u0e17\u0e4c) |url=https://www.nangdee.com/name/f/14724/\u0e44\u0e1a\u0e23\u0e17\u0e4c-\u0e27\u0e0a\u0e34\u0e23\u0e27\u0e34\u0e0a\u0e0d\u0e4c-\u0e0a\u0e35\u0e27\u0e2d\u0e32\u0e23\u0e35.html |website=nangdee.com |publisher=Nang Dee |accessdate=March 15, 2020 |language=Thai}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=9 Things You Need To Know About Bright Vachirawit |url=https://www.thaiupdate.info/bright-vachirawit-profile/ |website=thaiupdate.info |publisher=Thai Update |accessdate=March 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nHe joined the entertainment industry as a TV show host for ''{{ill|Strawberry Krubcake|th|\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e40\u0e1a\u0e2d\u0e23\u0e35\u0e48\u0e04\u0e23\u0e31\u0e1a\u0e40\u0e04\u0e49\u0e01}}'' on [[Channel 3 (Thailand)|Channel 3]]. He became part of the music video ''Gawt Mai Dai'' by Bedroom Audio. In 2016, he debuted as an actor in the movie ''Love Say Hey''<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e40\u0e25\u0e34\u0e1f\u0e40\u0e0b\u0e40\u0e2e.. \u0e2d\u0e22\u0e32\u0e01\u0e40\u0e0b\u0e27\u0e48\u0e32\u0e23\u0e31\u0e01\u0e40\u0e18\u0e2d (2016) |url=https://www.nangdee.com/title/html/4430/\u0e40\u0e25\u0e34\u0e1f\u0e40\u0e0b\u0e40\u0e2e..-\u0e2d\u0e22\u0e32\u0e01\u0e40\u0e0b\u0e27\u0e48\u0e32\u0e23\u0e31\u0e01\u0e40\u0e18\u0e2d.html |website=nangdee.com |publisher=Nang Dee |accessdate=March 15, 2020 |language=Thai}}</ref> and starred in the TV series ''I Sea U'' as ''Peter'' along with [[Ungsumalynn Sirapatsakmetha]] (Pattie) and [[:th:\u0e40\u0e21\u0e06 \u0e40\u0e21\u0e06\u0e27\u0e31\u0e12\u0e19\u0e32|Mek Mekwattana]] (Jessie).<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e41\u0e0b\u0e48\u0e1a\u0e09\u0e38\u0e14\u0e2b\u0e31\u0e27\u0e43\u0e08! \"\u0e44\u0e1a\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e17-\u0e27\u0e0a\u0e34\u0e23\u0e27\u0e34\u0e0a\u0e0d\u0e4c \u0e0a\u0e35\u0e27\u0e2d\u0e32\u0e23\u0e35\" \u0e2b\u0e19\u0e38\u0e48\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e25\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e25\u0e39\u0e01\u0e04\u0e23\u0e36\u0e48\u0e07\u0e44\u0e17\u0e22-\u0e2d\u0e40\u0e21\u0e23\u0e34\u0e01\u0e31\u0e19 |url=https://praew.com/people/274469.html |website=praew.com |publisher=Praew |accessdate=March 15, 2020 |language=Thai |date=September 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe is currently one of the hosts of ''Toelaew'', a [[GMM 25]] program and plays the role of ''Sarawat'' in ''[[2gether: The Series (Thai TV series)|2gether: The Series]]'' where he is being paired with [[Metawin Opas-iamkajorn]] (Win).<ref name=\"releasedate\">{{cite web |title=#\u0e04\u0e31\u0e48\u0e19\u0e01\u0e39 \"\u0e40\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e32\u0e30\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e04\u0e39\u0e48\u0e01\u0e31\u0e19 2gether The Series\" \u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e01\u0e23\u0e30\u0e41\u0e2a \u0e15\u0e31\u0e49\u0e07\u0e41\u0e15\u0e48\u0e17\u0e35\u0e40\u0e0b\u0e2d\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e25\u0e48\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e38\u0e14 \u0e04\u0e31\u0e48\u0e19\u0e01\u0e39 EP1 \u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14\u0e39 \u0e44\u0e1a\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e17\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19 #\u0e2a\u0e32\u0e23\u0e27\u0e31\u0e15\u0e23 #\u0e44\u0e17\u0e19\u0e4c\u0e04\u0e19\u0e0a\u0e34\u0e04 |url=https://medhubnews.com/\u0e14\u0e39\u0e1a\u0e17\u0e04\u0e27\u0e32\u0e21-64752-\u0e04\u0e31\u0e48\u0e19\u0e01\u0e39-\u0e40\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e32\u0e30\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e04\u0e39\u0e48\u0e01\u0e31\u0e19-2gether-the-series-\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e01.html |website=medhubnews.com |publisher=Med Hub News |accessdate=March 15, 2020 |language=Thai |date=February 7, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e2a\u0e32\u0e27\u0e46\u0e2d\u0e01\u0e2b\u0e31\u0e01 \"\u0e44\u0e1a\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e17 \u0e27\u0e0a\u0e34\u0e23\u0e27\u0e34\u0e0a\u0e0d\u0e4c\"\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e40\u0e2d\u0e01\u0e0b\u0e35\u0e23\u0e35\u0e22\u0e4c\u0e2e\u0e34\u0e15\u0e21\u0e35\u0e04\u0e19\u0e14\u0e39\u0e41\u0e25\u0e2b\u0e31\u0e27\u0e43\u0e08\u0e41\u0e25\u0e49\u0e27 |url=https://today.line.me/th/pc/article/\u0e2a\u0e32\u0e27\u0e46\u0e2d\u0e01\u0e2b\u0e31\u0e01+\u0e44\u0e1a\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e17+\u0e27\u0e0a\u0e34\u0e23\u0e27\u0e34\u0e0a\u0e0d\u0e4c+\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e40\u0e2d\u0e01\u0e0b\u0e35\u0e23\u0e35\u0e22\u0e4c\u0e2e\u0e34\u0e15\u0e21\u0e35\u0e04\u0e19\u0e14\u0e39\u0e41\u0e25\u0e2b\u0e31\u0e27\u0e43\u0e08\u0e41\u0e25\u0e49\u0e27-jXXv8Y |website=line.me |publisher=Line Today |accessdate=March 15, 2020 |language=Thai |date=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Movie===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n! Ref\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | 2016\n| style=\"font-style:italic;\" | Love Say Hey\n| Tae\n| Main Role\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e40\u0e25\u0e34\u0e1f \u0e40\u0e0b \u0e40\u0e2e \u0e15\u0e31\u0e27\u0e2d\u0e22\u0e48\u0e32\u0e07 Love Say Hey Trailer |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E8E257G1Aos |via=YouTube |publisher=Movietronic |accessdate=March 17, 2020 |language=Thai |date=March 2, 2016}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n! Ref\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align: center;\" | 2013\n| style=\"font-style:italic;\" | Strawberry Krubcake\n| Bright\n| Main Host\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=Strawberry Krubcake EP. 1 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NGrYekIvnsY |via=YouTub